articles.description: Marvin Smith scored 18 points with four 3-pointers, leading four into double figures, and North Carolina Greensboro took control midway through the first half, defeating The Citadel 82-66 on Thursday.
articles.headline: Smith leads balanced UNC Greensboro past The Citadel 82-66

articles.description: Tony Carr rewards Mike Watkins for running the floor in transition with a lob for an alley-oop dunk.
articles.headline: Penn State's Watkins beats everyone for alley-oop

images.caption: Tony Carr rewards Mike Watkins for running the floor in transition with a lob for an alley-oop dunk.
images.name: Penn State's Watkins beats everyone for alley-oop

articles.description: Cougars guard Rob Gray follows his own miss and feeds Breaon Brady for the putback layup.
articles.headline: Houston uses hustle to get Brady the layup

images.caption: Cougars guard Rob Gray follows his own miss and feeds Breaon Brady for the putback layup.
images.name: Houston uses hustle to get Brady the layup

articles.description: Kaleb Wesson exits the game with an apparent ankle injury after going for a rebound.
articles.headline: Ohio State's Wesson leaves game with injury

images.name: Ohio State's Wesson leaves game with injury

articles.description: Brevin Pritzl drains the deep three and then makes a steal to get a transition layup as Wisconsin leads Purdue 14-12.
articles.headline: Pritzl's offensive explosion gives Badgers lead

images.caption: Brevin Pritzl drains the deep three and then makes a steal to get a transition layup as Wisconsin leads Purdue 14-12.
images.name: Brevin Pritzl drains the deep three and then makes a steal to get a transition layup as Wisconsin leads Purdue 14-12.

articles.description: Trae Young's spirits were buoyed by a surprise phone call Wednesday from Hall of Famer Oscar Robertson, who gave the Sooners freshman "some good advice."
articles.headline: Trae Young gets 'good advice' from Hall of Famer Oscar Robertson

images.caption: Trae Young is ice cold from the field, shooting 4-of-16 and scoring 19 points, as the No. 7 Red Raiders defeat the No. 23 Sooners 88-78.
images.name: Oklahoma falls to Texas Tech, suffers fourth consecutive loss
